Visualize Data With Charts

Treemap Charts
Use treemaps to visualize hierarchical quantitative data, where containing rectangles designate relationship using color, and "leaf" rectangles represent quantity using area.

Create a Treemap Chart
In the lens, click  and then select the Treemap chart type.
In the Segment Size field, add a measure, such as total opportunity amount.
In the Segments field, add one or more dimensions to analyze the measure by. For example, select Billing Country and Billing State/Province.

To change the chart display, click  and set the chart properties in the Formatting panel.
title: Treemap Charts in Salesforce Analytics
